1
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:12,633
<i> Do you know Alicia Enriquez?</i>

2
00:00:12,767 --> 00:00:14,567
<i>She was the only woman
I ever loved,</i>

3
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:17,033
<i>and I heard she died because...</i>

4
00:00:17,167 --> 00:00:18,800
<i> Because of a robber.</i>

5
00:00:18,933 --> 00:00:21,167
<i>I was there when she was held up
and killed...</i>

6
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:23,400
<i>because Alicia Enriquez
is my mother.</i>

7
00:00:23,533 --> 00:00:26,367
<i>The best thing we can do
is put someone undercover.</i>

8
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:27,367
<i> Conde is right.</i>

9
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:28,533
<i> But with the way you look,</i>

10
00:00:28,667 --> 00:00:30,133
<i>no one will believe
you're a student.</i>

11
00:00:30,267 --> 00:00:34,433
<i>So you need to find someone new
who can pretend to be a student.</i>

12
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:35,833
<i>I know you've been wanting
to change your life</i>

13
00:00:35,967 --> 00:00:37,067
<i> for a long time now.</i>

14
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,700
<i>I want to make you an undercover
agent at a university.</i>

15
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:41,967
<i>So you and your partner
need to do well.</i>

16
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:42,667
<i> Partner, Boss?</i>

17
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:43,867
<i> Lieutenant Antonio Conde,</i>

18
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:46,133
<i>Corporal Wilbert Mariano
reporting for duty, Sir.</i>

19
00:00:46,267 --> 00:00:47,933
<i>We shouldn't waste
any more time.</i>

20
00:00:48,067 --> 00:00:49,767
<i> We need to get information.</i>

21
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,867
<i>- You're hurting me. Let me go!
- What?</i>

22
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,233
<i>That's enough, Bro.
You're hurting a woman.</i>

23
00:00:54,367 --> 00:00:55,600
<i> I'll admit something to you.</i>

24
00:00:55,733 --> 00:00:58,667
<i>A long time ago,
I've cheated on your mother.</i>

25
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:01,833
<i>Our daughter is Sergeant
Bobby Enriquez.</i>

26
00:01:01,967 --> 00:01:04,200
<i>You need to go to
the Regional Headquarters.</i>

27
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:04,933
<i> Why?</i>

28
00:01:05,067 --> 00:01:06,133
<i> For your oathtaking,</i>

29
00:01:06,267 --> 00:01:08,633
<i>because you've been promoted
to Master Sergeant.</i>

30
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:10,200
<i>What do you care?
Do you know him, Jhem?</i>

31
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:11,600
<i>If I were you, I wouldn't
interfere with this.</i>

32
00:01:11,733 --> 00:01:12,733
<i>You don't know the person
you're fighting with.</i>

33
00:01:12,867 --> 00:01:14,067
<i>Well, you don't know me at all.</i>

34
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:15,700
<i> What? Are you still brave?</i>

35
00:01:28,167 --> 00:01:29,800
Hey, don't interfere anymore.

36
00:01:58,033 --> 00:01:59,000
Come here.

37
00:02:00,233 --> 00:02:00,833
What?

38
00:02:00,967 --> 00:02:01,867
You're so arrogant.

39
00:02:03,367 --> 00:02:04,767
That's enough! What's with you?

40
00:02:06,567 --> 00:02:08,467
Don't you ever hurt
a woman again!

41
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:12,700
Sorry if I stepped
on your love team!

42
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:13,500
Vince?

43
00:02:18,167 --> 00:02:19,167
OA!

44
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:20,133
Bro...

45
00:02:21,967 --> 00:02:22,567
Stop!

46
00:02:22,700 --> 00:02:23,833
Move! Move!

47
00:02:23,967 --> 00:02:24,567
What's that?

48
00:02:26,667 --> 00:02:28,400
You're really stubborn, huh?

49
00:02:28,533 --> 00:02:30,800
- Let's go!
- Go to the office!

50
00:02:30,933 --> 00:02:33,367
- Get up! Go to the office!
- You!

51
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:34,600
- Let's go!
- Come here!

52
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:22,100
I told you not to interfere,
right?

53
00:03:22,267 --> 00:03:25,100
We can't get the other students'
attention.

54
00:03:25,233 --> 00:03:28,433
Our mission will be ruined
because of your meddling ways.

55
00:03:28,567 --> 00:03:30,733
Dude, I can't stand
what I saw earlier.

56
00:03:31,967 --> 00:03:34,200
Bro, isn't this you?

57
00:03:34,333 --> 00:03:35,633
I knew it!

58
00:03:35,767 --> 00:03:37,867
You're the ones
who beat up Ryan!

59
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:40,000
You're so great! Those guys
are so arrogant!

60
00:03:40,133 --> 00:03:43,267
- Let's get a picture! Let's go.
- Let's take a photo!

61
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,900
Bro, make sure I'm seen
in the photo.

62
00:03:46,767 --> 00:03:48,400
- One more!
- Tag me on that, okay?

63
00:03:50,167 --> 00:03:51,167
It's our turn.

64
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:56,867
-They're nothing compared to us.
-You're so great.

65
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,333
If you need help,
just call me.

66
00:04:01,367 --> 00:04:02,533
Hey.

67
00:04:02,667 --> 00:04:04,567
You two were involved in the
trouble earlier, weren't you?

68
00:04:06,033 --> 00:04:07,367
Come on, come with me.

69
00:04:15,567 --> 00:04:17,000
Isn't that great, Bok?

70
00:04:17,133 --> 00:04:19,067
Imagine, Enriquez got promoted.

71
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:22,767
Bobby got promoted?

72
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:23,833
Yes, Bok.

73
00:04:23,967 --> 00:04:26,633
Not just here
at the police station.

74
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:28,233
Where else?

75
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:30,000
There in your heart.

76
00:04:30,133 --> 00:04:31,733
You're on a first-name
basis now.

77
00:04:33,067 --> 00:04:34,300
But, wait...

78
00:04:34,433 --> 00:04:36,100
Seriously, Bok, you don't know?

79
00:04:36,233 --> 00:04:38,933
Didn't she tell you?
Her oathtaking is tomorrow.

80
00:04:41,133 --> 00:04:42,467
We're both busy.

81
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,200
Busy, busy...

82
00:04:44,333 --> 00:04:45,967
I'm busier than both of you.

83
00:04:46,100 --> 00:04:47,967
I even have a love life.

84
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:52,033
But you know, sometimes,
I don't understand you both.

85
00:04:52,167 --> 00:04:54,067
Sometimes, you're super close.

86
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,967
Sometimes, you're not.

87
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:57,433
What's going on with you?

88
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:01,000
Nothing, nothing.
Will you just stop it?

89
00:05:01,167 --> 00:05:04,233
You know, Bok,
it's better if you text her.

90
00:05:04,367 --> 00:05:07,433
Just say congratulations
or something like that,

91
00:05:07,567 --> 00:05:08,333
it's up to you.

92
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:10,367
Hurry up!

93
00:05:12,233 --> 00:05:13,233
Whatever...

94
00:05:13,367 --> 00:05:15,167
You better go, I'm doing
something here.

95
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,400
You're bothering me.

96
00:05:16,533 --> 00:05:17,400
Okay, okay, okay.

97
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:20,467
I'll just sort out the emails.

98
00:05:36,867 --> 00:05:39,900
Congrats, Bobby.

99
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,167
- No need. I'll just delete it.
- Bok!

100
00:05:50,300 --> 00:05:52,133
Bok! Why did you delete it?

101
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:56,533
Chief needs that email!

102
00:05:56,667 --> 00:05:57,967
Send it again, okay?

103
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:00,000
- Oh, okay.
- I'm going to get scolded!

104
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:08,733
Sir, they're here.

105
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:10,700
Oh, okay. Come in here!

106
00:06:13,667 --> 00:06:14,533
Faye...

107
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:24,467
What happened?

108
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,800
Why did you get into trouble?

109
00:06:25,933 --> 00:06:29,733
Sir Chito, those two really
didn't do anything wrong.

110
00:06:29,867 --> 00:06:33,233
They just stopped Ryan
from hurting me.

111
00:06:33,367 --> 00:06:34,333
What do you mean?

112
00:06:34,467 --> 00:06:36,567
These two are such smart alecks!

113
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:38,100
You know, you're at fault too.

114
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:40,167
This wouldn't have happened
if it weren't for you!

115
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:42,167
You're really accusing us
as smart alecks?

116
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:43,800
You're the one hurting a girl

117
00:06:43,933 --> 00:06:45,133
just because she doesn't like
you anymore!

118
00:06:45,267 --> 00:06:47,333
Don't you have a mother
or a sister?

119
00:06:49,467 --> 00:06:50,800
Don't talk anymore.

120
00:06:50,933 --> 00:06:51,967
Ryan...

121
00:06:52,967 --> 00:06:54,633
I'm so disappointed in you.

122
00:06:57,033 --> 00:06:58,300
We're men.

123
00:06:58,433 --> 00:07:00,933
By nature, we're stronger
than women,

124
00:07:01,067 --> 00:07:03,133
so we have to protect them,

125
00:07:03,267 --> 00:07:05,267
not use that against them!

126
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:09,000
It doesn't make you
a stronger man.

127
00:07:09,133 --> 00:07:10,933
Anyway

128
00:07:11,067 --> 00:07:13,733
we still don't tolerate violence
among our students.

129
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,667
You and your group
are suspended.

130
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,467
Sir?

131
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:18,233
Sir, come on...

132
00:07:18,367 --> 00:07:19,567
You heard me.

133
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:21,100
You're suspended.

134
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:26,100
You two...

135
00:07:27,167 --> 00:07:29,067
you're still not off the hook.

136
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,467
I'm giving you an assignment.

137
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:31,300
Sir...

138
00:07:40,033 --> 00:07:40,967
There.

139
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:43,200
Clean the whole gym, okay?

140
00:07:43,333 --> 00:07:44,633
Even the bleachers.

141
00:07:44,767 --> 00:07:47,133
Sir, we just got involved.

142
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:50,333
I know, but you still got
into a fight.

143
00:07:50,467 --> 00:07:53,300
So that's your punishment.

144
00:07:54,667 --> 00:07:55,833
Unless...

145
00:07:55,967 --> 00:07:57,700
unless you want to be suspended.

146
00:07:57,833 --> 00:07:59,033
No.

147
00:07:59,167 --> 00:08:00,233
It's okay.

148
00:08:00,367 --> 00:08:01,567
It's okay, Sir.

149
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:02,833
Do it well, okay?

150
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:08,600
What did I say?

151
00:08:10,267 --> 00:08:11,500
Low profile.

152
00:08:12,767 --> 00:08:15,867
Blend in and don't be
noticeable.

153
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:19,933
Just bcause of your
meddling ways...

154
00:08:20,067 --> 00:08:22,200
What now?
We're famous all over campus!

155
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:25,833
You're such an action star.

156
00:08:25,967 --> 00:08:27,900
Why? Did I tell you to help?

157
00:08:28,033 --> 00:08:29,667
Look at you, when we were
fighting earlier,

158
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:32,433
you smiled at the girls.
You're trying to be cute.

159
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:34,967
Are you okay?

160
00:08:38,067 --> 00:08:39,033
Faye...

161
00:08:39,167 --> 00:08:42,933
I didn't expect you
to study here, too.

162
00:08:43,067 --> 00:08:44,233
What's your course?

163
00:08:46,467 --> 00:08:48,033
AB...

164
00:08:48,167 --> 00:08:49,800
AB Comm Arts.

165
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:52,700
Oh, by the way,
this is my cousin Will.

166
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:53,433
Bill!

167
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:55,967
Bill Castillo.

168
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:59,133
Vic, let's finish this.

169
00:08:59,267 --> 00:09:00,567
Vic?

170
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:02,600
Is Vic your real name?

171
00:09:02,733 --> 00:09:04,367
I thought it's Vince?

172
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,733
And where are Lee and Bal?

173
00:09:14,867 --> 00:09:16,400
We're undercover.

174
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:21,267
But this is top secret, okay?

175
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:24,600
He's a cop while I'm helping
Boss Tonyo.

176
00:09:24,733 --> 00:09:25,633
Wow...

177
00:09:25,767 --> 00:09:27,000
You're so great.

178
00:09:27,133 --> 00:09:29,433
You said it really casually,
huh?

179
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,300
Dude, she knows me.

180
00:09:31,433 --> 00:09:33,633
She knows that I used to be
a snatcher.

181
00:09:33,767 --> 00:09:36,233
What do you want? Should I still
insist on my fake identity?

182
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:39,067
She even knows my real name.

183
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:41,600
Guys, you have nothing
to worry about.

184
00:09:41,733 --> 00:09:43,933
I'm good with keeping secrets,
promise.

185
00:09:45,267 --> 00:09:48,167
But why are you going
undercover?

186
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,733
Are there any criminals
on campus?

187
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:57,433
Where are these two?

188
00:09:58,467 --> 00:09:59,767
In the gym, Bro.

189
00:10:06,033 --> 00:10:07,067
Faye...

190
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,867
you're asking us
for classified information.

191
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,233
You shouldn't know
we're undercover.

192
00:10:12,367 --> 00:10:14,933
But, Bro, we already told her
that we're just pretending.

193
00:10:15,067 --> 00:10:16,367
Why don't we just tell her
everything?

194
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:17,967
Hey, don't be stubborn.

195
00:10:19,533 --> 00:10:22,567
Bro, we can trust her.

196
00:10:22,700 --> 00:10:25,667
Guys, it's okay.
You don't have to tell me.

197
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:30,133
But if you need help,
just tell me, okay?

198
00:10:30,267 --> 00:10:31,967
You can trust me.

199
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:32,767
Okay.

200
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:42,033
The guys who are trending
are here.

201
00:10:46,133 --> 00:10:48,000
This is the first time
I saw your faces.

202
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:51,000
You're good at fighting!

203
00:10:51,133 --> 00:10:53,367
Why? What do you want?

204
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:54,500
Nothing.

205
00:10:55,867 --> 00:10:57,733
We just want to see
how good you are.

206
00:10:57,867 --> 00:10:58,433
Okay.

207
00:10:58,567 --> 00:10:59,267
No.

208
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:02,367
We're not going to fight.

209
00:11:03,767 --> 00:11:05,533
We were already sent
to the office.

210
00:11:07,067 --> 00:11:08,033
Sorry, guys.

211
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:10,333
What, Jako?
Let's go and beat these guys.

212
00:11:10,467 --> 00:11:11,400
Game!

213
00:11:11,533 --> 00:11:14,033
Wait a minute!
Can you stop causing trouble?

214
00:11:14,167 --> 00:11:16,167
Don't interfere. Stay here.

215
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:17,533
Hey, don't hurt her!

216
00:11:17,667 --> 00:11:19,200
Go ahead. Hurry up!

217
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:20,900
You're really looking
for trouble, huh?

218
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:29,200
Sergeant Enriquez,
I'll just call the mayor.

219
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:30,600
Okay, thank you.

220
00:11:35,567 --> 00:11:37,733
Bobby, what's happening?

221
00:11:37,867 --> 00:11:40,100
Why did Captain Isang ask us
to be here?

222
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:41,400
Yes.

223
00:11:41,567 --> 00:11:43,833
Imagine, when she found out
that the mayor called for you,

224
00:11:43,967 --> 00:11:46,000
she woke us up to come with you.

225
00:11:46,133 --> 00:11:47,200
Yes.

226
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:51,700
And we've also been told
not to leave you here alone.

227
00:11:51,833 --> 00:11:53,267
Why?

228
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,033
Bobby.

229
00:11:55,433 --> 00:11:56,733
- Hello, Mayor.
- Mayor.

230
00:11:58,033 --> 00:12:00,500
Thank you very much for coming.

231
00:12:00,633 --> 00:12:02,867
I was going to go to you,

232
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:06,500
but your grandmother
might be angry,

233
00:12:06,633 --> 00:12:09,733
especially since I know
she doesn't accept me

234
00:12:09,867 --> 00:12:11,700
as your father.

235
00:12:11,833 --> 00:12:14,133
Bobby is your daughter, Mayor?

236
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:16,700
Yes.

237
00:12:19,133 --> 00:12:22,767
Bobby, I have something for you.

238
00:12:22,900 --> 00:12:23,533
Wait a minute.

239
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:26,067
Come in, come in.

240
00:12:32,633 --> 00:12:33,433
There, okay.

241
00:12:36,767 --> 00:12:38,200
There.

242
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:39,400
That's all for you.

243
00:12:43,967 --> 00:12:44,733
Mayor...

244
00:12:44,867 --> 00:12:49,800
Bobby, you can just call me
"Dad."

245
00:12:49,967 --> 00:12:51,633
Stop calling me "Mayor."

246
00:12:51,767 --> 00:12:54,833
Does your family know
that you're doing all this?

247
00:12:54,967 --> 00:12:57,567
Yes, they accept you,

248
00:12:57,700 --> 00:13:02,433
and they support me for making
it up to you as your father.

249
00:13:06,933 --> 00:13:09,800
Mayor, you shouldn't have gone
out of your way.

250
00:13:09,933 --> 00:13:11,467
This is too much.

251
00:13:12,933 --> 00:13:18,733
Don't take it personally
that I can't call you that yet.

252
00:13:18,867 --> 00:13:23,033
Maybe when the time is right.

253
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:24,467
I understand.

254
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:30,133
By the way, are you doing
anything tomorrow?

255
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:31,467
I do.

256
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:34,433
I have an oathtaking
for my promotion.

257
00:13:34,567 --> 00:13:36,200
You got promoted?

258
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:37,600
Congratulations!

259
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:39,967
Thank you, thank you.

260
00:13:40,100 --> 00:13:42,833
Well, if that's the case,
let's celebrate.

261
00:13:42,967 --> 00:13:46,700
I'll prepare lunch tomorrow
so you can meet my family.

262
00:13:48,367 --> 00:13:49,667
You are all invited.

263
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,200
We'll be there, Mayor.

264
00:13:52,633 --> 00:13:54,000
Bring your grandmother with you.

265
00:13:55,467 --> 00:13:57,067
Okay, I'll try.

266
00:13:58,733 --> 00:14:00,067
Okay, Mayor.

267
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,700
Thank you. We'll go ahead.

268
00:14:04,733 --> 00:14:05,867
Okay.

269
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,167
Let me carry it for you.

270
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:08,567
Maybe there's some cash, Mayor.

271
00:14:09,900 --> 00:14:11,000
Okay, bring them.

272
00:14:11,133 --> 00:14:12,167
I'll bring it, Mayor.

273
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:13,233
Okay.

274
00:14:15,867 --> 00:14:16,933
Mayor.

275
00:14:17,067 --> 00:14:18,533
- Thank you.
- Okay.

276
00:14:20,467 --> 00:14:21,600
Thank you, Mayor.

277
00:14:36,467 --> 00:14:37,333
Wait, wait.

278
00:14:37,467 --> 00:14:40,600
Easy, just chill.
We don't want trouble.

279
00:14:40,733 --> 00:14:43,633
Jako, these guys are nothing!
They're not going to fight!

280
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:46,967
You're not really
going to fight?

281
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:48,967
We're inside the university!

282
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:50,133
Let's go outside,

283
00:14:50,267 --> 00:14:51,867
I'll knock you out
even if there are more of you.

284
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,100
Oh, what?

285
00:14:53,233 --> 00:14:55,333
Hey, we're just testing you.

286
00:14:55,467 --> 00:14:58,600
We watched your moves
against Ryan's group.

287
00:14:58,733 --> 00:14:59,667
Solid!

288
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:02,567
We want you to try out
for the taekwondo team.

289
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:07,000
Are you challenging us just
to join the taekwondo team?

290
00:15:09,467 --> 00:15:11,067
You guys are crazy!

291
00:15:12,267 --> 00:15:13,467
We're not interested.

292
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:16,467
Are you sure?

293
00:15:19,267 --> 00:15:19,833
Fine!

294
00:15:21,667 --> 00:15:23,533
But you don't have protection
from the chaos here

295
00:15:23,667 --> 00:15:24,433
at the university.

296
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:27,033
You're missing out.

297
00:15:28,633 --> 00:15:29,633
Let's go!

298
00:15:29,767 --> 00:15:31,133
These guys are cowards.

299
00:15:38,700 --> 00:15:41,600
This guy is threatening us
as if he's a big shot!

300
00:15:41,733 --> 00:15:43,967
You'd better stay away
from Jako.

301
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:45,200
You know,

302
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:48,200
his brother was in jail
for using illegal substances,

303
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:51,167
the current trend,
the pimple patch drugs.

304
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:54,933
Is Monty Espina his brother?

305
00:15:55,067 --> 00:15:56,333
Do you know him?

306
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:05,967
Sir, who's my visitor, Sir?

307
00:16:06,100 --> 00:16:07,867
The one wearing a hat.

308
00:16:25,933 --> 00:16:28,833
You're a jerk.
Why did you get arrested now?

309
00:16:28,967 --> 00:16:31,567
You still owe a lot.
Where are your items?

310
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:34,467
Sir, I'm just keeping them.
They can still be sold.

311
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,900
Who will sell it?
People like you?

312
00:16:37,033 --> 00:16:39,367
Sir, he won't get arrested.
I trust him.

313
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:40,933
As you should!

314
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:42,567
Boss is not happy anymore.

315
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:45,300
Don't wait for him to frown.

316
00:16:47,067 --> 00:16:48,600
Sir, I'm sorry.

317
00:16:51,300 --> 00:16:53,267
Sir, let me out of here first.

318
00:16:54,467 --> 00:16:57,000
Maybe you can find a way.

319
00:16:57,133 --> 00:17:02,400
Isn't the mayor the father
of the boss?

320
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:10,400
What did your father say?

321
00:17:10,533 --> 00:17:12,633
Is he going to your oathtaking?

322
00:17:13,667 --> 00:17:15,733
He said he wanted to come.

323
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:18,667
He said he'll cancel
his meetings tomorrow,

324
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:20,967
but I said there's no need.

325
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,167
Why?

326
00:17:23,867 --> 00:17:29,533
Because I said I wanted you
to pin my promotion tomorrow.

327
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:33,300
Why me?

328
00:17:33,433 --> 00:17:36,400
Grandmother is just pretending,
but deep down she's thrilled.

329
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:40,233
Really?

330
00:17:40,367 --> 00:17:42,400
Of course, Grandmother.

331
00:17:42,533 --> 00:17:43,867
Even when I was young,

332
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:46,733
weren't you always with me
every step of the way

333
00:17:46,867 --> 00:17:49,433
in my dream of becoming
a police officer?

334
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:52,633
So now, of course,
you can't miss that.

335
00:17:52,767 --> 00:17:53,867
Sorry, Bobby.

336
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,500
I'm getting grumpy.

337
00:17:56,633 --> 00:18:00,000
You know, I'm getting older.

338
00:18:00,133 --> 00:18:03,433
The important thing is,
you're still beautiful.

339
00:18:03,567 --> 00:18:04,667
Because the grandchild
is also beautiful.

340
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:06,667
Well, of course,
I inherited it from you.

341
00:18:10,033 --> 00:18:10,733
Grandmother...

342
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:15,300
are you still mad at the mayor?

343
00:18:15,433 --> 00:18:19,267
I'm mad at him because of what
he did to your mother.

344
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:23,400
But I'm also happy

345
00:18:23,533 --> 00:18:25,633
because he now recognizes you
as his daughter.

346
00:18:27,733 --> 00:18:28,733
Well, wait a minute.

347
00:18:28,867 --> 00:18:31,400
Aren't you going to bring
Sir Tonyo with you?

348
00:18:31,533 --> 00:18:33,467
You guys are together so often.

349
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:35,967
You guys are often mistaken
for a couple.

350
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:39,300
Oh, no. I don't want him
to go there.

351
00:18:39,433 --> 00:18:42,367
We're not a couple, and he's not
family, Grandmother.

352
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:44,033
Well, you can be a couple,

353
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:46,733
so that he can be part
of our family too.

354
00:18:46,867 --> 00:18:48,067
Come on, Grandmother.

355
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:49,900
Just kidding!

356
00:18:51,267 --> 00:18:52,600
Grandchild...

357
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:54,233
Congratulations.

358
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:55,200
Thank you.

359
00:18:55,367 --> 00:18:56,800
- Good night.
- Thank you, Grandmother.

360
00:18:56,933 --> 00:18:58,467
Good night.

361
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:00,833
- Go to sleep, okay?
- Okay.

362
00:19:12,033 --> 00:19:13,400
OMG!

363
00:19:13,533 --> 00:19:15,733
This is my first time here,
Abdul!

364
00:19:15,867 --> 00:19:16,833
I love this place.

365
00:19:16,967 --> 00:19:18,333
- It's beautiful.
- You're right.

366
00:19:18,467 --> 00:19:19,700
Don't be so loud.

367
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:21,533
Captain, you're such a killjoy.
It's our first time.

368
00:19:21,667 --> 00:19:23,033
Just this once.

369
00:19:23,167 --> 00:19:26,133
Just appreciate it,
but don't scream.

370
00:19:26,267 --> 00:19:26,867
Wait.

371
00:19:34,033 --> 00:19:35,367
It's Sir Tonyo?

372
00:19:37,700 --> 00:19:38,533
Hello, Sir?

373
00:19:38,667 --> 00:19:39,767
Hello, Enriquez.

374
00:19:39,900 --> 00:19:41,567
Is there a problem?

375
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:44,600
Sir, have you heard?
Bobby met his father!

376
00:19:44,733 --> 00:19:48,167
<i>None other than Mayor Guerrero!</i>

377
00:19:48,300 --> 00:19:49,833
Is that true, Enriquez?

378
00:19:49,967 --> 00:19:51,767
<i> Mayor Guerrero is your father?</i>

379
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:53,167
How did that happen?

380
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:55,133
There have been so many
changes in your life,

381
00:19:55,267 --> 00:19:56,900
you haven't even told me.

382
00:19:57,033 --> 00:19:59,200
It's a long story.

383
00:20:00,967 --> 00:20:02,000
Okay, Sir.

384
00:20:02,167 --> 00:20:03,833
I have some things to do.

385
00:20:05,167 --> 00:20:07,233
Just say hi to Selena for me.

386
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:11,267
You're jealous?

387
00:20:12,733 --> 00:20:13,333
What?

388
00:20:13,467 --> 00:20:14,667
Really?

389
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:17,100
Bobby's father
is Mayor Guerrero?

390
00:20:17,233 --> 00:20:18,600
Yes.

391
00:20:18,733 --> 00:20:21,533
The mayor's assistant picked
her up earlier.

392
00:20:21,667 --> 00:20:23,633
Sir, I'm sorry,

393
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:27,000
but you and Ma'am Enriquez
have something in common.

394
00:20:27,133 --> 00:20:29,333
Both of you are children
of action stars.

395
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:32,033
That's not all.

396
00:20:32,167 --> 00:20:33,900
They are also rivals
in politics.

397
00:20:34,033 --> 00:20:36,233
Well, that's okay

398
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:42,333
because Bobby and Conde seem
like rivals in real life too.

399
00:20:42,467 --> 00:20:45,300
They've been ignoring each other
since our last police operation.

400
00:20:45,433 --> 00:20:46,467
Bok,

401
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:49,133
what are you inventing again?

402
00:20:49,267 --> 00:20:51,767
Is that really how it is
when a doctor ghosts you?

403
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:53,200
Hey...

404
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:54,433
That hurts!

405
00:20:59,233 --> 00:21:00,933
So what?

406
00:21:01,067 --> 00:21:02,267
Who is she?

407
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:06,233
Her loss, not mine.

408
00:21:10,467 --> 00:21:11,500
Excuse me!

409
00:21:15,867 --> 00:21:16,300
Dizon.

410
00:21:17,333 --> 00:21:18,267
Conde.

411
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:19,000
Sir.

412
00:21:20,233 --> 00:21:23,533
I will assign you to transfer
Simon de la Rama

413
00:21:23,667 --> 00:21:26,933
and Amado Tindog
to Calabari State Prison.

414
00:21:27,067 --> 00:21:29,067
Their hearing will start
next week,

415
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,933
so they need to be transferred.

416
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:34,400
Bok, isn't Mandong Warak there?

417
00:21:35,567 --> 00:21:37,633
Sir, who's Mandong Warak?

418
00:21:37,767 --> 00:21:38,567
Oh my...

419
00:21:39,733 --> 00:21:41,367
He's a police killer.

420
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:46,400
Mandong Warak smashes the
breasts of his police victims.

421
00:21:46,567 --> 00:21:48,100
Besides, that's only fitting
for him

422
00:21:48,233 --> 00:21:49,767
because his face
is already smashed.

423
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,800
Dizon, Conde, go ahead...

424
00:21:54,933 --> 00:21:55,867
you can go.

425
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,000
Yes, Sir.

426
00:22:01,133 --> 00:22:01,667
Let's go.

427
00:22:05,633 --> 00:22:06,333
I'm okay, Bok.

428
00:22:08,067 --> 00:22:09,900
There was just something
in my eyes earlier, Conde.

429
00:22:15,333 --> 00:22:19,100
Why does it seem like everyone
is ghosting me?

430
00:22:19,233 --> 00:22:21,600
Bobby, I'm glad you came.

431
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:24,100
Hi, Bobby.

432
00:22:24,233 --> 00:22:27,600
Bobby, what brings you here?

433
00:22:27,733 --> 00:22:28,667
Sophia...

434
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:31,800
I invited them for lunch.

435
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:33,800
Oh, really?

436
00:22:33,933 --> 00:22:37,200
I thought this was going
to be a normal family lunch.

437
00:22:37,333 --> 00:22:40,100
I didn't know there
were surprise guests.

438
00:22:42,033 --> 00:22:45,200
Bobby, Ms. Isang,
meet my family.

439
00:22:46,667 --> 00:22:50,533
Their boarders, Abdul and Mar,
are with them.

440
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:51,367
Hello.

441
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:52,367
- Vice Mayor!
- Vice Mayor!

442
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:54,700
We're the ones who saved
Captain Isang.

443
00:22:54,833 --> 00:22:55,933
- We're with you!
- Yes!

444
00:22:56,067 --> 00:22:57,000
Of course.

445
00:22:57,133 --> 00:22:59,133
You guys are familiar.

446
00:23:00,733 --> 00:23:03,167
Bobby, nice to see you again.

447
00:23:04,367 --> 00:23:07,300
I didn't think I'd have
a sibling who is a Sergeant.

448
00:23:08,700 --> 00:23:10,200
Excuse me, Sir.

449
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:11,800
She's been promoted.

450
00:23:11,933 --> 00:23:13,567
She's no longer a Sergeant.

451
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:15,433
It's Master Sergeant now.

452
00:23:15,567 --> 00:23:16,600
Is that so?

453
00:23:16,733 --> 00:23:18,167
Congratulations, Bobby.

454
00:23:18,300 --> 00:23:19,400
Thank you.

455
00:23:19,533 --> 00:23:23,100
Joaquin, you didn't say that
your daughter was invited.

456
00:23:23,267 --> 00:23:25,900
I would've worn something nicer.

457
00:23:26,033 --> 00:23:28,867
Oh, no, you don't need to.

458
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:31,833
Whatever you wear,
you still look beautiful.

459
00:23:33,967 --> 00:23:36,400
Bobby, let's go. Let's eat.

460
00:23:36,533 --> 00:23:38,467
- Daddy, I'm so hungry.
- Oh, come on. Let's go.

461
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:39,767
- Let's go?
- Go ahead.

462
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,167
Let's go.

463
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:44,000
Madam...

464
00:23:45,133 --> 00:23:46,533
is that Bobby?

465
00:23:49,133 --> 00:23:49,767
Yes.

466
00:23:51,300 --> 00:23:53,267
You already know what to do,
Cheka.

467
00:24:01,633 --> 00:24:02,533
Bobby?

468
00:24:05,033 --> 00:24:06,733
What's Bobby doing here?

469
00:24:24,333 --> 00:24:25,367
Hello, Sir?

470
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:27,500
I was going to ask you
for a little donation.

471
00:24:27,633 --> 00:24:28,933
Aren't you in jail?

472
00:24:29,100 --> 00:24:30,767
Where are you going
to use the money for?

473
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:32,033
Here's what you're going to do.

474
00:24:32,167 --> 00:24:33,933
Make friends with Jako,

475
00:24:34,067 --> 00:24:36,367
and you'll definitely get
information

476
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:38,833
on Monty's pimple patch
drug supplier.

477
00:24:38,967 --> 00:24:40,967
Vic and I thought about
joining your team.

478
00:24:41,100 --> 00:24:43,033
But you have to prove yourself.

479
00:24:48,567 --> 00:24:50,900
Sir Tonyo, Ma'am Bobby
and Lieutenant Samson

480
00:24:51,033 --> 00:24:51,933
are competing in swimming.

481
00:24:52,067 --> 00:24:54,033
Bobby and Samson
in a swimming competition?

482
00:24:54,167 --> 00:24:56,100
When you lose, don't be sad,
okay?

483
00:24:56,233 --> 00:24:57,367
That's fine.

484
00:24:57,500 --> 00:25:00,300
You're the one who shouldn't
be sad when I feed you moss.

485
00:25:00,433 --> 00:25:01,167
There you go, Bobby!

486
00:25:01,300 --> 00:25:02,433
Let's go!

487
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:03,600
You're almost there, Bobby!
There you go, there you go!
